## ✅ **🔵 SECTION 1: Input & Trigger**

### ⚙️ **Nodes**

1️⃣ **Trigger: Manual Execute**
![⚡](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/high-voltage_26a1.png)

* **What it does:** This node starts the workflow manually when you click “Execute Workflow.”
* **Why it’s useful:** It’s the simplest way to test your workflow on demand. Later, you can swap this with a **Schedule** node for daily or weekly runs.

2️⃣ **Set: Competitor Domain**
![📝](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/memo_1f4dd.png)

* **What it does:** This node stores the **competitor’s domain** you want to analyze.
* **Example:** `ahrefs.com` or `moz.com`
* **Why it’s useful:** You can easily change domains without modifying the whole workflow. For multiple competitors, loop through them!

---

### 💡 **Beginner Benefit**

✅ **Simple input control:** You don’t need to touch code — just type your competitor’s domain in one place.
✅ **Reusable:** Same input can be reused for any site — just update the domain value.

---

---

## ✅ **🤖 SECTION 2: Agent Scrape Engine**

### ⚙️ **Nodes**

3️⃣ **Agent: Scrape Backlinks (Bright Data MCP)**
![🤖](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/robot_1f916.png)

* **What it does:** Calls your **custom scraping Agent** that uses Bright Data MCP to visit backlink explorer pages (like Ahrefs or Moz) and pull backlink data.
* **How:** The Agent uses a secure proxy network to get around anti-bot protections and scrapes backlink profiles (URL, anchor text, type, etc.).
* **Output:** Raw JSON with all backlinks found for the competitor.

**Sub-Nodes:**

* ⚙️ **MCP Client: Execute Scraper**
  ![🧩](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/puzzle-piece_1f9e9.png)

  * Connects directly to Bright Data’s backend to run the scraper tool.
* 💬 **OpenAI Chat Model**
  ![🧠](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/brain_1f9e0.png)

  * Optional: If your Agent needs an LLM to generate instructions or parse dynamic websites, it talks to OpenAI here.
* 🗂️ **Output Parser: Backlink JSON**
  ![🗂️](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/card-index-dividers_1f5c2-fe0f.png)

  * Ensures the Agent’s raw text comes out as **structured JSON** → easy to split & save later.

---

### 💡 **Beginner Benefit**

✅ **No coding scraping:** You don’t have to build scrapers from scratch. Bright Data + Agent handles the hard part.
✅ **Dynamic parsing:** The OpenAI node helps the Agent handle weird or changing HTML structures.
✅ **Safe & scalable:** MCP proxies handle geo-blocks and captchas for you.

---

---

## ✅ **🟢 SECTION 3: Transform & Store**

### ⚙️ **Nodes**

4️⃣ **Function: Split Backlinks**
![🔀](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/repeat-button_1f501.png)

* **What it does:** Takes the JSON output of all backlinks and splits them into **one item per backlink**.
* **Why:** So each backlink becomes its own row when sent to Google Sheets.

5️⃣ **Google Sheets: Append Backlinks**
![📄](https://em-content.zobj.net/thumbs/120/apple/354/page-facing-up_1f4c4.png)

* **What it does:** Adds each backlink as a **new row** in your Google Sheet.
* **Columns:** Domain, URL, anchor text, date, category, etc.

---
